1.name: Book of Combos 1
1.description: An introductory text for first-time combiners. Improves your success rate.

2.name: Book of Combos 2
2.description: A basic text. Owning Book 1 and this improves your combining success rate.

3.name: Book of Combos 3
3.description: An intermediate text. Owning Books 1, 2 and this improves your combining success rate.

4.name: Book of Combos 4
4.description: An advanced text. Owning Books 1-3 and this improves your combining success rate.

5.name: Book of Combos 5
5.description: A pro-level text. Owning Books 1-4 and this improves your combining success rate.

6.name: Organizer Guide
6.description: An issue of Hunting Life magazine which explains how to maximize Item Box space.

7.name: Pack Rat Guide
7.description: An issue of Hunting Life magazine containing advanced item-cramming techniques.

8.name: Potion
8.description: Restores a small amount of Health. Try to combine these into something Mega-better!

9.name: Mega Potion
9.description: Restores a moderate amount of Health. This potion is a hunter's best friend.

10.name: Nutrients
10.description: Very slightly increases your maximum Health level.

11.name: Mega Nutrients
11.description: Slightly increases your maximum Health level.

12.name: Antidote
12.description: Removes all traces of poison from your system.

13.name: Immunizer
13.description: Boosts your natural ability to heal.

14.name: Dash Juice
14.description: Lets you run without tiring for a short period of time.

15.name: Mega Dash Juice
15.description: Lets you run without tiring for longer than with regular Dash Juice.

16.name: Demondrug
16.description: Boosts your Attack by filling you with -- guess what? -- demonic strength.

17.name: Mega Demondrug
17.description: Boosts your Attack even more than a regular Demondrug.

18.name: Might Pill
18.description: Temporarily endows you with the strength of a mighty god. Potent!

19.name: Armorskin
19.description: Boosts your Defense by turning your skin as hard as rock.

20.name: Mega Armorskin
20.description: Boosts your Defense even more than a regular Armorskin.

21.name: Adamant Pill
21.description: Temporarily makes your skin as hard as adamant. Potent!

22.name: Cool Drink
22.description: Provides temporary relief from extreme heat.

23.name: Hot Drink
23.description: Provides temporary relief from extreme cold.

24.name: Cleanser
24.description: Immediately removes any ice or mud on your body. Clean as a whistle!

25.name: Deodorant
25.description: An item that cures Stench. Releases a puff of deoderizing smoke when thrown down.

26.name: Psychoserum
26.description: Temporarily sharpens your sixth sense and attunes you to the ways of monsters.

27.name: Herbal Medicine
27.description: Removes all traces of poison and restores a slight amount of Health.

28.name: Max Potion
28.description: Fully restores Health and increases your maximum Health level all the way.

29.name: Ancient Potion
29.description: Fully restores Health and Stamina, and raises the max levels of both all the way,

30.name: Catalyst
30.description: Works with other materials to enhance their effects. Cannot be used by itself.

31.name: Energy Drink
31.description: This bottle is all you'll need to wake up! Shakes off sleep and restores Stamina.

32.name: Gunpowder
32.description: A dangerous substance that explodes when struck or heated.

33.name: Lifecrystals
33.description: Mysterious crystals long worshipped as a source of life.

34.name: Lifepowder
34.description: A Lifecrystal combination used as medicine. Heals with a single touch.

35.name: Tranquilizer
35.description: Medicine that works as an anesthetic when Combined.

36.name: Mystery Charm
36.description: A modest good-luck charm. What does it do? Finish the Quest and you'll find out.

37.name: Shining Charm
37.description: A curious good-luck charm. What does it do? Finish the Quest and you'll find out.

38.name: Timeworn Charm
38.description: A powerful good-luck charm. What does it do? Finish the Quest and you'll find out.

40.name: Powercharm
40.description: An amulet that raises Attack. Just carrying this gives you demonic strength.

41.name: Powertalon
41.description: A powerful amulet that raises Attack. Made with a Deviljho Talon.

42.name: Armorcharm
42.description: An amulet that raises Defense. Just carrying this hardens your skin like rock.

43.name: Armortalon
43.description: A powerful amulet that raises Defense. Made with a Deviljho Talon.

44.name: Raw Meat
44.description: Meat carved from a monster. Can be cooked, combined, or use to set a trap.

45.name: Poisoned Meat
45.description: Raw Meat that poisons whatever eats it. Makes great bait for traps.

46.name: Tinged Meat
46.description: Raw Meat that paralyzes whatever eats it. Makes great bait for traps.

47.name: Drugged Meat
47.description: Raw Meat that puts whatever eats it to sleep. Makes great bait for traps.

48.name: Rare Steak
48.description: Provides a small boost to your Stamina. This one's still red in the middle

49.name: Well-done Steak
49.description: Provides a moderate boost to your Stamina. Meat done right!

50.name: Burnt Meat
50.description: Meat that has been burnt to a crisp. It might boost your Stamina, or it might drain it ..

51.name: Chilled Meat
51.description: Meat that cools the body, wards off heat, and boosts a moderate amount of Stamina.

52.name: Hot Meat
52.description: Meat that warms the body, wards off the cold, and boosts a moderate amount of Stamina.

54.name: Boomerang
54.description: An usually-shaped weapon from abroad that returns to its user when thrown.

55.name: Throwing Knife
55.description: A standard throwing knife. Flies straight and true.

56.name: Poison Knife
56.description: A throwing knife with a venom-coated blade. Poisons targets.

57.name: Sleep Knife
57.description: A throwing knife whose blade has been dusted with sleeping agents.

58.name: Paralysis Knife
58.description: A throwing knife coated with toxins that paralyze a target.

59.name: Tranq Knife
59.description: A throwing knife used for capturing monsters ensnared in traps.

60.name: Bomb Casing
60.description: A base material for making hand-thrown bombs.

61.name: Paintball
61.description: Toss this scented paint at a monster to mark it, allowing you to track its position.

62.name: Flash Bomb
62.description: Flashes brightly on impact. Toss this right under a monster's nose to blind it.

63.name: Sonic Bomb
63.description: A grenade-like item that emits a high frequency blast of sound on detonation.

64.name: Dung
64.description: That's right: monster poop. The odor reveals too much about the monster's diet.

65.name: Dung Bomb
65.description: Releases an odor monsters find repulsive. It may even drive them away... or not.

66.name: Smoke Bomb
66.description: Creates a large cloud of smoke wherever it lands.

68.name: Farcaster
68.description: Instantly transports you back to base camp.

69.name: Tranq Bomb
69.description: A hand grenade used to capture monsters ensnared in traps.

71.name: Net
71.description: A sturdy net able to support a certain amount of weight without breaking.

72.name: Trap Tool
72.description: A tool you'll need to put a Pitfall Trap or other traps together with.

73.name: Pitfall Trap
73.description: Activates when something heavy walks across. Use this to capture monsters.

74.name: Shock Trap
74.description: Immobilizes a target. You can use this to capture monsters.

75.name: Small Barrel
75.description: How many whiffs does it take to find out what was in this empty barrel? Just one!

76.name: Large Barrel
76.description: How many licks does it take to find out what was in this empty barrel? Just one!

77.name: Barrel Bomb S
77.description: A small time bomb. You can use it underwater.

78.name: Barrel Bomb S+
78.description: A powered-up Barrel Bomb S. Small, but it packs a punch. You can use it underwater.

79.name: Barrel Bomb L
79.description: A potent bomb that detonates on impact. Waterproofed, so it still works underwater.

80.name: Barrel Bomb L+
80.description: A powered-up Barrel Bomb L. Deadly. Waterproofed, so it still works underwater.

82.name: Bounce Bomb+
82.description: An improved version of the Bounce Bomb. Requires some skill to use.

83.name: Felvine Bomb
83.description: Emits a scent Felynes love. Try hitting monsters with it.

85.name: Huskberry
85.description: A berry that is hollow on the inside.

88.name: Normal S Lv2
88.description: Non-specialized ammo. More powerful than Lv1.

89.name: Normal S Lv3
89.description: Non-specialized ammo that ricochets, resulting in high damage.

90.name: Pierce S Lv1
90.description: Armor-piercing ammo that deals multiple hits to some monsters.

91.name: Pierce S Lv2
91.description: Armor-piercing ammo. Higher-level ammo deals additional hits.

92.name: Pierce S Lv3
92.description: Armor-piercing ammo. This highest level deals the most hits.

93.name: Pellet S Lv1
93.description: Ammo that hits a wide area. Deals multiple hits at close range.

94.name: Pellet S Lv2
94.description: Ammo that hits a wide area. Higher-level ammo deals additional hits.

95.name: Pellet S Lv3
95.description: Ammo that hits a wide area. This highest level deals the most hits

96.name: Crag S Lv1
96.description: Powerful ammo that lodges in a target, then explodes.

97.name: Crag S Lv2
97.description: Very powerful ammo that lodges in a target, then explodes.

98.name: Crag S Lv3
98.description: Extremely powerful ammo that lodges in a target, then explodes.

99.name: Clust S Lv1
99.description: Fragments into three shells upon impact. Beware of friendly fire!

100.name: Clust S Lv2
100.description: Fragments into four shells upon impact. Beware of friendly fire!

101.name: Clust S Lv3
101.description: Fragments into five shells upon impact. Beware of friendly fire!

102.name: Flaming S
102.description: Ammo that packs extra punch against monsters susceptible to Fire.

103.name: Water S
103.description: Ammo that packs extra punch against monsters susceptible to Water.

104.name: Thunder S
104.description: Ammo that packs extra punch against monsters susceptible to Thunder.

105.name: Freeze S
105.description: Ammo that packs extra punch against monsters susceptible to Ice.

106.name: Dragon S
106.description: Mysterious ammo that won't work in regular Bowguns.

107.name: Poison S Lv1
107.description: Ammo dipped in poison. Some targets require multiple shots.

108.name: Poison S Lv2
108.description: Ammo dipped in deadly poison. Some targets require multiple shots.

109.name: Para S Lv1
109.description: Ammo that causes paralysis. Some targets require multiple shots.

110.name: Para S Lv2
110.description: Ammo that paralyzes quickly. Some targets require multiple shots.

111.name: Sleep S Lv1
111.description: Ammo containing a sleeping agent. Some targets require multiple shots.

112.name: Sleep S Lv2
112.description: Ammo packed with sleeping agents. Some targets require multiple shots.

113.name: Exhaust S Lv1
113.description: Special ammo that drains monsters' stamina.

114.name: Exhaust S Lv2
114.description: Enhanced special ammo that drains monsters' stamina.

115.name: Slicing S
115.description: Special ammo that ejects sharp blades on impact. Can it sever tails?

116.name: WyvernFire
116.description: Ammo patterned after Wyvern's Fire. Not as potent, but can be rapid-fired.

118.name: Recover S Lv1
118.description: Ammo that restores a small amount of Health to the target.

119.name: Recover S Lv2
119.description: Ammo that restores a moderate amount of Health to the target.

120.name: Demon S
120.description: Ammo that fills the target with savage amounts of strength.

121.name: Armor S
121.description: Ammo that hardens the skin, guarding against attacks and Wind Pressure.

122.name: Paint S
122.description: Ammo that marks a monster's position on your Map for a limited time.

123.name: Tranq S
123.description: Bowgun ammo used to capture monsters ensnared in traps.

126.name: Power Coating
126.description: An arrow coating that increases the Attack of arrows fired. Capacity 50.

127.name: C.Range Coating
127.description: An arrow coating that increases close-range power and melee Sharpness. Capacity 20.

128.name: Poison Coating
128.description: An arrow coating that applies Poison effects to arrows fired. Capacity 20

129.name: Para Coating
129.description: An arrow coating that applies Paralysis effects to arrows fired. Capacity 20

130.name: Sleep Coating
130.description: An arrow coating that applies Sleep effects to arrows fired. Capacity 20

131.name: Exhaust Coating
131.description: An arrow coating that causes arrows fired to drain monsters' stamina. Capacity 20

133.name: Paint Coating
133.description: An arrow coating that marks a monster's position on the map for a limited time. Capacity 99.

155.name: Worm
155.description: A fishing lure. Wriggles underwater, enticing those fishies to bite.

156.name: Mega Fishing Fly
156.description: A fishing lure. Causes a feeding frenzy. No fish can resist this one!

157.name: Frog
157.description: Know any monsters good at fishing? Try fighting fire with fire.

158.name: Sushifish Bait
158.description: A fishing lure with chum that makes Sushifish go, mmm.

159.name: Burst Bait
159.description: A fishing lure with chum that makes fish that rupture upon death go mmm

160.name: Goldenfish Bait
160.description: A fishing lure with chum that makes Goldenfish go, mmm.

161.name: Old Pickaxe
161.description: A cheap pickaxe with an easily nicked blade.

162.name: Iron Pickaxe
162.description: A pickaxe with a reasonably strong blade.

163.name: Mega Pickaxe
163.description: A pickaxe tempered with steel. This one won't nick easily.

164.name: Old Bug Net
164.description: A cheap net for catching bugs. It tears easily.

165.name: Bug Net
165.description: A durable net for catching bugs.

166.name: Mega Bug Net
166.description: An extremely durable net for catching bugs. This one is made to last.

167.name: BBQ Spit
167.description: Just what you need to cook meat. A must-have item for any hungry hunter.

168.name: Whetstone
168.description: A standard-sized Whetstone. Use it to restore a weapon's Sharpness.

169.name: Binoculars
169.description: Allow you to see farther and observe from a distance.

170.name: Garbage
170.description: Junk created when a combination attempt fails.

171.name: Field Horn
171.description: Used to attract certain monsters -- blow at your own risk. May break when used.

172.name: Health Horn
172.description: Restores Health to those who hear it. May break when used.

173.name: Antidote Horn
173.description: Eliminates poison in the blood of those who hear it. May break when used.

174.name: Demon Horn
174.description: Increases the strength of those who hear it. May break when used.

175.name: Armor Horn
175.description: Bolsters the defenses of those who hear it. May break when used.

176.name: Honey
176.description: Full of nutrients, but indigestible in this form.

177.name: Herb
177.description: Restores a very small amount of Health, but the flavor's not too hot.

178.name: Antidote Herb
178.description: A plant used in antidotes. It sometimes cures poison when eaten by itself.

180.name: Ivy
180.description: A vine of tough fibers. Woven, it is sturdy enough to hold a person's weight.

182.name: Sap Plant
182.description: The sap it secretes is a strong adhesive. Careful you don't glue your Pouch shut!

183.name: Felvine
183.description: Melynxes' favorite food -- they just have to steal it.

185.name: Hot Pepper
185.description: Blazingly spicy. Sure, it'll warm you up, but it's too hot to handle on its own.

189.name: Blue Mushroom
189.description: A well-known Combo material used to augment power. The deeper the blue, the better.

190.name: Nitroshroom
190.description: A hard-to-find mushroom with the power to generate blazing heat.

192.name: Toadstool
192.description: Logic says not to eat this poisonous fungus, but don't write it off completely.

193.name: Exciteshroom
193.description: This one has a very strange aroma... Edible? Only one way to find out.

195.name: Dragon Toadstool
195.description: A dangerous fungus said to suck the life out of the one who plucks it. Beware.

196.name: Paintberry
196.description: A berry with a shockng hue and an overwhelming scent. Look out: it WILL stain!

197.name: Might Seed
197.description: Temporarily raises your Attack when ingested by improving energy flow.

198.name: Adamant Seed
198.description: Temporarily raises your Defense when ingested by hardening tissue.

199.name: Nulberry
199.description: A mysterious berry that cures all elemental Blights (Fire, Water, Ice, Thunder, and Dragon)

200.name: Dragonfell Berry
200.description: Eat this to cure Dragonblight and temporarily increase Dragon Resistance.

201.name: Scatternut
201.description: A nut that violently ejects its contents when struck.

202.name: Needleberry
202.description: A berry covered with needle-like thorns.

204.name: Bomberry
204.description: A berry that explodes when struck.

205.name: Bumblepumpkin
205.description: A trendy orange pumpkin. If left undisturbed, it can grow to gigantic proportions.

206.name: Stone
206.description: A rock with just the right heft for throwing. Tried and tested!

207.name: Iron Ore
207.description: Ore with high iron content. Can be smelted and forged into various equipment.

208.name: Earth Crystal
208.description: Crystallized microbes which are prized as an abrasive when forging weapons.

209.name: Machalite Ore
209.description: An ore harder than iron, but also several times more difficult to forge with.

210.name: Dragonite Ore
210.description: An ore that yields metal superior to that of Machalite. Rare and valuable.

211.name: Lightcrystal
211.description: An extemely hard substance with a faint glow. Sometimes used for crafting tools.

212.name: Ice Crystal
212.description: Ice that will not melt at room temparatures. Can be used to create denser ore.

213.name: Firestone
213.description: Combusts even at room temperature. Its high heat can be used to fuse materials.

216.name: Carbalite Ore
216.description: An ore still being researched. It yields even better metal than Dragonite.

218.name: Fucium Ore
218.description: An ore composed of a mysterious metal, capable of fusing nearly any two materials together.

219.name: Firecell Stone
219.description: A magma-like deposit that only trained hands can properly work with.

224.name: Armor Stone
224.description: Reacts uniquely to heat. Combine with other materials to create coating for armor.

225.name: Armor Sphere
225.description: Reacts uniquely to heat. Fuse this to armor to increase its strength.

226.name: Armor Sphere+
226.description: Fuse this high-quality Armor Sphere to existing armor to increase its strength.

227.name: Adv Armor Sphere
227.description: An advanced Armor Sphere. Rare in Moga Village. Save it for that special upgrade.

231.name: Whetfish
231.description: A fish with a dorsal fin hard enough to sharpen weapons with.

232.name: Sushifish
232.description: A fatty, delicious fish that restores a small amount of Health when consumed.

233.name: Sleepyfish
233.description: A fish that contains sleeping agents.

234.name: Pin Tuna
234.description: A fish with jaws covered in tiny, needle-like spikes.

236.name: Popfish
236.description: A fish that literally pops when it dies.

237.name: Scatterfish
237.description: A fish that dashes itself to pieces when it dies.

238.name: Burst Arowana
238.description: A fish that bursts open when it dies

239.name: Bomb Arowana
239.description: A fish that explodes when it dies.

240.name: Glutton Tuna
240.description: A fish that eats anything -- allowing you to sometimes get items from its stomach.

242.name: Small Goldenfish
242.description: A rare fish that commands a high price, but beware its ferocity, rookies!

243.name: Wanchovy
243.description: A fish that can induce exhaustion.

245.name: Blue Cutthroat
245.description: A fish that emits blue light. Its sharp body will cut you to pieces if you're not careful

248.name: Insect Husk
248.description: The remains of an insect. You must be one hardcore collector to hang onto this!

250.name: Stinkhopper
250.description: A grasshopper with a foul odor. Make fishing lures with it；its scent drives explosive fish wild.

251.name: Snakebee Larva
251.description: An unusual larva. Make fishing lures with it； its scent drives Goldenfish wild.

252.name: Godbug
252.description: An insect said to live 1000 years -- but no one's lived long enough to prove it.

253.name: Bitterbug
253.description: Boosts your natural ability to heal when eaten. It also cures poison... sometimes.

254.name: Flashbug
254.description: A nocturnal insect sometimes found in daylight. They emit a bright flash upon death.

255.name: Thunderbug
255.description: Releases an electric shock when struck. Used to light rooms and start fires.

257.name: Killer Beetle
257.description: This insect's hard shell is often used as an abrasive.

258.name: Hercudrome
258.description: Said to be the world's strongest bug. Used in forging, cooking, and more.

259.name: Fulgurbug
259.description: Thunderbugs which have been stimulated by Zinogre. They emit a pale blue light.

260.name: Rare Scarab
260.description: A rare and valuable insect that greatly assists in the bonding of metals.

262.name: Butterfly Beetle
262.description: A strange insect with the large jaws of a beetle and the delicate wings of a butterfly.

263.name: Monster Bone S
263.description: A handy material used to make everything from equipment to sundries.

264.name: Monster Bone M
264.description: A nicely-sized bone. Strong yet flexible, it's as reliable as steel and wood.

265.name: Monster Bone L
265.description: Wyvern bone needed to craft larger items. The right item will fuse this to a shell.

266.name: Mystery Bone
266.description: A weathered bone. Not sturdy enough to use in forging.

267.name: Unknown Skull
267.description: An animal skull worn and weathered beyond identification.

268.name: Monster Bone+
268.description: A top-quality monster bone. Hard to find, but vital for crafting powerful equipment.

269.name: Monster Keenbone
269.description: A rare bone with a razor-sharp tip that retains its strength even when crafted.

270.name: Monster Hardbone
270.description: A precious bone rarely yielded by large wyverns. Difficult to forge, but prized for its strength.

272.name: Avian Finebone
272.description: A bone from a Jaggi or other bird wyvern. Small in size, but high in quality.

274.name: Jumbo Bone
274.description: A large, thick bone. Often cut apart in workshops for use in crafting.

275.name: Stoutbone
275.description: The large, sturdy bone of a beast. Prized by blacksmiths as a prime forging material.

276.name: Dragonbone Relic
276.description: A curiously unfossilized bone from a dragon that once roamed these lands.

277.name: Wyvern Fang
277.description: Used in Bowgun bullet points. Gunpowder shatters them, generating shrapnel.

278.name: Wyvern Claw
278.description: Used in Bowgun bullet points. Gunpowder triggers a blast with a wide radius.

279.name: Bird Wyvern Gem
279.description: A valuable gem that can be harvested from Jaggi and other bird wyverns.

282.name: Steel Egg
282.description: A egg of glittering steel. Very valuable and rare, but of no use to a hunter.

283.name: Silver Egg
283.description: A egg of glittering silver. Very valuable and rare, but of no use to a hunter.

284.name: Golden Egg
284.description: An egg of glittering gold. Insanely valuable and rare, but of no use to a hunter.

287.name: Poison Sac
287.description: A monster organ that contains a lethal toxin. Handle with extreme care.

288.name: Toxin Sac
288.description: A monster organ that contains a lethal toxin. Handle with extreme care.

289.name: Paralysis Sac
289.description: A monster organ that contains paralyzing neurotoxins.

290.name: Sleep Sac
290.description: A monster organ that contains a knockout powder capable of inducing sleep.

291.name: Flame Sac
291.description: A monster organ filled with flammable powder. Handle with caution.

292.name: Inferno Sac
292.description: A monster organ filled with powder that ignites if it so much as touches air. Danger!

294.name: Thunder Sac
294.description: A monster organ that can store up large amounts of high-voltage electricity.

295.name: Frost Sac
295.description: A monster organ that contains a sub-zero liquid. Handle with extreme care.

296.name: Freezer Sac
296.description: A monster organ with tremendous freezing power.

297.name: Aqua Sac
297.description: A monster organ designed to hold and preserve water.

298.name: Torrent Sac
298.description: A monster organ designed to hold and preserve copious amounts of water.

299.name: Dash Extract
299.description: A mysterious substance that can be culled from certain monsters.

300.name: Pale Extract
300.description: Has the ability to amplify the effects of certain medicines.

301.name: Gargwa Feather
301.description: A big, beautiful feather plucked from a Gargwa. Often used as a fashion accessory.

302.name: Kelbi Horn
302.description: Infusions of powdered Kelbi Horn work wonders on tummyaches. It's a local secret!

303.name: Blue Kelbi Horn
303.description: An especially rare Kelbi Horn. Popular among traders.

304.name: Warm Pelt
304.description: A pelt from a small animal. Used for many things, but mostly just regular clothes.

305.name: High-quality Pelt
305.description: A pelt from a small animal. Used for many things, but mostly just regular clothes.

306.name: Rhenoplos Shell
306.description: A very strong shell, considering it comes such a small monster.

308.name: Rhenoplos Scalp
308.description: A sturdy part of the skill that yields, shall we say, dashing results?

310.name: Slagtoth Hide+
310.description: Firm, lustrous hide often cut into large slabs. Prized for its water-resistant properties.

311.name: Bnahabra Shell
311.description: Every bit as sturdy as wyvern armor in the hands of a clever craftsman.

313.name: Bnahabra Wing
313.description: Difficult to forge with -- the results vary depending on which surface you use.

314.name: Altaroth Jaw
314.description: These durable mouthparts are surprisingly difficult to carve loose.

315.name: Altaroth Stomach
315.description: A transparent sac cut from an Altaroth's abdomen, used to store who knows what.

324.name: Jaggi Scale
324.description: A scale carved from a Jaggi. Not very valuable, but beginners can't be choosers.

325.name: Jaggi Scale+
325.description: A vividly-colored superior Jaggi scale that can be used to produce hardier equipment.

326.name: Jaggi Hide
326.description: Commonly used in this region. It can be made into any number of things.

327.name: Bird Wyvern Fang
327.description: A fang similar in value to the foreign Velociprey's. Used to make bowgun ammo.

329.name: G.Jaggi Hide
329.description: Durable, elegantly patterned hide from a Great Jaggi. Befits its position as pack leader.

330.name: G.Jaggi Hide+
330.description: The rugged hide of a strong Great Jaggi. Fewer wounds means higher quality and value.

331.name: G.Jaggi Claw
331.description: A hook-shaped claw cut from a Great Jaggi. Just like a Jaggi claw, only much, much larger.

332.name: G.Jaggi Claw+
332.description: A hook-shaped claw cut from a Great Jaggi. Well-Sharpened from countless battles.

333.name: King's Frill
333.description: Proof of who's boss among Jaggi -- and now proof you are on your way as a hunter.

358.name: Lagombi Pelt
358.description: A white pelt carved from a Lagombi. One touch and you'll be hooked on its soft, fluffy fur.

359.name: Lagombi Pelt+
359.description: A quality white Lagombi pelt. Its glossy, frosty shine makes it a sought-after luxury item.

361.name: Lagombi Ear+
361.description: An impressive Lagombi ear. Highly-developed, it can become sharp as steel if polished.

362.name: Lagombi Plastron
362.description: A shell piece from a Lagombi's belly. Its ridges are what allow the Lagombi to slide on ice.

363.name: Lagombi Plastron+
363.description: A robust Lagombi Plastron. Strong, sticky and thick, it's used to make superior equipment.

463.name: Monster Fluid
463.description: Sticky fluid that is often found in insects after they feast.

464.name: Monster Broth
464.description: A broth made from only the thickest of a monster's juices. Quite rich.

487.name: Rathian Scale
487.description: A scale from a flying wyvern native to this area. Rathian mate with male Rathalos.

488.name: Rathian Scale+
488.description: A fine Rathian scale. It may not look special, but its hardness puts other scales to shame.

489.name: Rathian Shell
489.description: A shell piece comprised of layered scales, making it much harder than just one.

490.name: Rathian Carapace
490.description: A sturdy Rathian carapace. Even harder than a normal Rathian shell.

491.name: Rathian Webbing
491.description: Hard to forge with, but its thermal properties make it ideal for armor lining.

492.name: Rathian Spike
492.description: Needle-like hair found on the Rathian's back and wings. They contain poison.

493.name: Rathian Spike+
493.description: As sharp as the keenest blade. It is longer and sturdier than other spikes.

494.name: Rathian Plate
494.description: A searing tail scale. Hard to come by and as fiery as the wyvern it came from.

495.name: Rathian Ruby
495.description: A rare gem formed inside a Rathian. It seems almost too nice to forge with.

496.name: P.Rathian Scale+
496.description: A high-grade scale from a Pink Rathian. Chic hunters love the blend of strength and style.

501.name: Rathalos Scale
501.description: A Rathalos scale. Wyvern scales like this one and the harder shells are basic forging items.

502.name: Rathalos Scale+
502.description: An extraordinarily durable scale carved from the body of a Rathalos.

503.name: Rathalos Shell
503.description: A shell piece comprised of layered scales, making it much harder than just one.

504.name: Rathalos Carapace
504.description: A rigid Rathalos carapace. Even harder than a normal Rathalos Shell.

505.name: Rathalos Webbing
505.description: Hard to forge with, but its thermal properties make it ideal for armor lining.

506.name: Rathalos Wing
506.description: A wing that has been removed. Skilled artisans can craft it into strong equipment.

507.name: Rathalos Tail
507.description: The severed tail of a Rathalos. It has any number of uses.

508.name: Rathalos Plate
508.description: A searing tail scale. Hard to come by and as fiery as the wyvern it came from.

509.name: Rathalos Ruby
509.description: A rare gem formed inside a Rathalos. It seems almost too nice to forge with.

512.name: A.Rathalos Tail
512.description: The severed tail of an Azure Rathalos. It fetches a high price due to its rarity.

513.name: A.Rathalos Wing
513.description: A wing that has been removed. Excellent for forging both weapons and armor.

518.name: Rath Marrow
518.description: Recent advances allow this marrow to be extracted. It ignites on air contact.

519.name: Rath Medulla
519.description: Recent advances allow this red hot organ to be removed, but it's hard to forge with.

522.name: Zinogre Carapace
522.description: The teal carapace of a Zinogre. Its magnificence reveals the futility of facing the monarch.

526.name: Zinogre Horn+
526.description: A pointed Zinogre horn. When carved, it can be used to grant equipment incomparable power.

528.name: Zinogre Claw+
528.description: A sharp, high voltage Zinogre claw. Its electrified attacks are truly brutal.

529.name: Zinogre Tail
529.description: The plate-covered tail of a Zinogre. It wields deadly force when swung.

531.name: Zinogre Shocker+
531.description: A Zinogre shell that stores and releases electricity. Grants a thunder god's power to gear.

533.name: Zinogre Jasper
533.description: A rare gem occasionally produced inside a Zinogre's body. The monarch's power swells within.

539.name: Dracophage Bug
539.description: Dragonfell Berry-loving bugs that store up Dragon energy. A Stygian Zinogre's power source

543.name: Brach Carapace
543.description: A hard Brachydios carapace. Glossy like obsidian, it adds a refined beauty to crafted gear.

544.name: Brach Ebonshell
544.description: An obsidian Brachydios brace. Makes especially strong armor, perhaps due to the slime mold.

545.name: Brach Ebonshell+
545.description: A premium Brachydios brace. The slime coating may contain weird bacteria, so be careful.

546.name: Brach Scalp
546.description: The large, protruding scalp of a Brachydios, covered in an explosive green substance.

547.name: Brach Scalp+
547.description: A hard and sharp scalp piece from a fierce Brachydios. Even more explosive than usual.

548.name: Mystery Slime
548.description: The explosive green substance found on Brachydios monsters. Handle with extreme care.

550.name: Brach Pounder
550.description: A Brachydios arm that buried countless foolhardy hunters. It's covered in green slime.

616.name: Deviljho Scale
616.description: A greenish-black Deviljho scale. It's not often sold, as rumors claim it brings it misfortune.

617.name: Deviljho Hide
617.description: Black hide that is oddly slimy and difficult to forge with.

619.name: Deviljho Talon
619.description: A dangerously sharp, hooked talon. Inexperienced crafters risk serious injury.

620.name: Deviljho Scalp
620.description: Removing this part of a Deviljho's skull releases an unimaginably putrid odor.

621.name: Deviljho Tail
621.description: A masive tail resembling a fin. Some folks are out to collect these exclusively.

622.name: Deviljho Saliva
622.description: The symbol of a Deviljho's insatiable appetite. The strong acid corrodes all it touches.

623.name: Black Blood
623.description: Dark black blood characteristic of a Deviljho. It feels like it could jump up and attack at any time.

625.name: Deviljho Gem
625.description: A precious gem said to contain a Deviljho's might. Used in shady rituals.

659.name: Earth Dragongem
659.description: One of the tougher materials to get from a Jhen Mohran, and that's saying something.

695.name: Arzuros Shell
695.description: A shell piece from an Arzuros's head or back. Bends willingly and is easy to forge.

696.name: Arzuros Pelt
696.description: A pelt carved from an Arzuros. The white portion is soft, while the blue is short and taut.

698.name: Spongy Hide
698.description: Uncannily elastic hide that retains water quite well.

699.name: Vivid Feather
699.description: A superbly colored Qurupeo feather. Nothing less than a natural work of art.

700.name: Strange Beak
700.description: An oddly shaped beak. It's pleasant enough.

701.name: Barroth Shell
701.description: A Barroth's shell -- more often than not covered in mud, but strong either way.

702.name: Barroth Scalp
702.description: This durable part of the skull is also the hardest to remove.

703.name: Nibelsnarf Hide
703.description: Hide from a Nibelsnarf. Many are surprised by its bright colors, in contrast to the outer shell.

704.name: Vivid Fluid
704.description: A fluid which helps retain water in a Nibelsnarf and allows the beast to thrive in the desert.

707.name: Uragaan Marrow
707.description: Hard-to-obtain bone marrow used for special crafts as well as medicinal purposes.

708.name: Uragaan Scute
708.description: Even more heat resistant than the Shell, this is said to protect sensitive organs.

713.name: Duramboros Horn
713.description: The horn of a Duramboros. Wider than a man's chest；all who see it are rendered speechless.

716.name: Diablos Shell
716.description: This shell piece is dense, as one knock will tell you, and heavier than it looks.

717.name: Majestic Horn
717.description: A twisted Diablos horn in great shape. Use it to make more powerful weapons.

726.name: Gobul Hide+
726.description: Fine skin from a Gobul. Said to rejuvenate the skin, and quite popular with the ladies.

727.name: Gobul Spike+
727.description: A high-quality barb from a Gobul. Only stroner monsters have such well-shaped spikes.

729.name: Amber Tusks+
729.description: Amber tusks sharpened by countless kills. They can smash through gigantic ice blocks.

730.name: Barioth Pelt+
730.description: A high-quality white pelt with a lovely texture. Nobles use it as a symbol of authority.

734.name: Shell Shocker+
734.description: A superior shell found only on certain Lagiacrus. Its structure permits greater electric output.

737.name: Agnaktor Fin+
737.description: An Agnaktor fin with an elegant dappled pattern. Aparently a popular item with collectors.

752.name: Ceadeus Hide
752.description: Even for monster skin, this is remarkably solid. Takes time and effort to craft.

753.name: Crooked Horn
753.description: A giant horn that was formed over ages. It evinces all weight of history.

754.name: Luminous Organ
754.description: Who knows why this organ glows, but it seems to hold incredible power.

755.name: Alatreon Plate
755.description: This particular Alatreon scale grows in backwards. It is as sharp as a blade.

756.name: Alatreon Webbing
756.description: At times this looks like a dark abyss； at others, like the coming of first light.

758.name: Rustshard
758.description: A hunk of rock? No, it seems to be metal... With a little polish, it could be more.

759.name: Ancient Shard
759.description: A fossil? No, it seems to be metal... With a little polish, it could be more.

760.name: Rusted Fragment
760.description: A uniquely shaped metal fragment covered in rust. It looks like it could be used for something..

768.name: Map
768.description: A map of the hunting ground.

769.name: First-aid Med
769.description: Restores a tiny bit of Health. It does a body... sort of good!

771.name: Ration
771.description: Slightly boosts current/max Stamina. Most hunters agree: it's gross.

772.name: Portable Spit
772.description: A Guild-provided BBQ Spit useful for novice hunters.

773.name: Mini Whetstone
773.description: A portable Whetstone you can use to restore Sharpness to weapons.

774.name: EZ Shock Trap
774.description: Immobilizes a target for easy capture.

775.name: EZ Flash Bomb
775.description: A grenade-like bomb that flashes brightly on impact.

779.name: EZ Barrel Bomb L
779.description: A powered-up Barrel Bomb L (as potent as a B. Bomb L+). OK underwater.

780.name: Ballista Ammo
780.description: Ammunition for a large mounted Bowgun.

781.name: Ballista Binder
781.description: Ammunition for a large mounted Bowgun. Keep giants from moving!

783.name: Cannon Ammo
783.description: Special ammunition for an anti-dragon cannon. Not fun to lug around.

784.name: Anti-dragon Bomb
784.description: A small time bomb that sticks to targets.

785.name: Torch
785.description: Use this to light up dark places and stave off certain monsters.

786.name: Paw Pass Ticket
786.description: Deliver to end the Quest. Maybe the Felynes will take you home...

787.name: Unique Mushroom
787.description: A pinky-sized mushroom valued for its unusual aroma.

788.name: Choice Mushroom
788.description: The perfect shape and aroma. Even better than a Unique Mushroom.

789.name: Ripened Mushroom
789.description: A unique Mushroom made more unique by maturing its aroma and flavor.

790.name: Goldenfish
790.description: A rare fish made of solid gold. Sell it for a tidy sum.

792.name: Royal Rhino
792.description: A beetle with a jewel-like gleam. Prized by bug fans of all ages.

795.name: Crystal Bone
795.description: A unique bone prized in the village for reasons unknown.

796.name: Bloodstone
796.description: Is this crimson stone the relic of some ancient beast?

810.name: Monster Guts
810.description: Monster innards galore. A prized delicacy.

811.name: Popo Tongue
811.description: Popo Tongue are popular, healthy, and fun to eat.

814.name: Wyvern Egg
814.description: An egg taken from a flying wyvern's nest. Very fragile, so handle with care.

815.name: Herbivore Egg
815.description: An egg stolen from an herbivore's nest. It looks pretty tasty.

817.name: Powderstone
817.description: A rock that explodes with even the slightest jolt. Careful!

825.name: Wyvern Tear
825.description: Mysterious tears wept only on special occasions.

831.name: Pinnacle Coin
831.description: A glorious coin given only to unquestioned Masters of Hunting. Beyond priceless.

832.name: Hunter King Coin
832.description: A silver coin given only to True Hunters. Its gleam is a symbol of your glory.

834.name: Beast Coin
834.description: An award granted for defeating a fanged beast in the Arena. A sharp fang is carved on it.

835.name: Flying Coin
835.description: An award granted for defeating a flying wyvern in the Arena. Proof one challenged the skies.

842.name: Voucher
842.description: Redeem this for a special meal with stronger effects than usual.

843.name: Gourmet Voucher
843.description: Exchange this for a kingly meal. Both its flavor and effects are top notch.

886.name: Commendation
886.description: A ticket awarded for a display of bravery. Collect enough and it might pay off.

896.name: Pawprint Stamp
896.description: Lynain paper currency, stamped with a pawprint. The letters written on it are unfamiliar.

897.name: VE Ticket
897.description: A ticket awarded in recognition of contributions to the Guild. Trade it with the Veggie Elder.

898.name: VE Deluxe Ticket
898.description: A ticket awarded in recognition of contributions to the Guild. Trade it with the Veggie Elder.

899.name: VE Bronze Ticket
899.description: A ticket awarded for hunting with friends. Trade it with the Veggie Elder.

900.name: VE Silver Ticket
900.description: A ticket awarded for hunting with friends. The Veggie Elder may offer a rare trade...

955.name: Aquaglow Jewel
955.description: An indispensible item used in Decorations.

956.name: Sunspire Jewel
956.description: An indispensible item used in Decorations.

957.name: Bloodrun Jewel
957.description: An indispensible item used in Decorations. A shame that these are so high-end.

958.name: Lazurite Jewel
958.description: An indispensible item used in Decorations. This one doesn't come along often.

959.name: Adamant Orb
959.description: An indispensible item used in Decorations. A rare orb that houses immense power.

1264.name: Rathian Shard
1264.description: A particularly thick Rathian scale. Its large size proves its owner's advanced age.

1265.name: Rathian Cortex
1265.description: A Rathian shell heavier than a carapace. Used to reinforce parts of equipment.

1266.name: Rathian Surspike
1266.description: Only a few of those superior spikes grow on a Rathian. It is both sharp and highly toxic.

1267.name: Rathian Mantle
1267.description: A legendary Rathian scale. Those who craft it are said to rule the earth and seize the sky.

1269.name: P.Rathian Shard
1269.description: A thick, shiny scale from a Pink Rathian. Rare is the artisan who has ever laid eyes on one.

1270.name: P.Rathian Cortex
1270.description: A hevy Pink Rathian cortex made up of a single beautiful plate. It commands top zenny when sold.

1271.name: G.Rathian Shard
1271.description: A thick Gold Rathian scale unlike anything seen before. Sunlight gives it an almost sacred glow.

1272.name: G.Rathian Cortex
1272.description: A cortex carved from a Gold Rathian. All who see it gasp at its intense glow.

1273.name: G.Rath Surspike
1273.description: A poisonous spike found on Gold Rathians in rare circumstances. It can pierce through anything.

1275.name: Rathalos Shard
1275.description: A Rathalos part made of several overlapping scales. Its strength is a natural wonder.

1276.name: Rathalos Cortex
1276.description: A robust Rathalos shell that is harder and sturdier than a carapace.

1277.name: Rathalos Lash
1277.description: A top-grade Rathalos tail. Strong ones like this are precious, and only used in select equipment.

1278.name: Rathalos Fellwing
1278.description: A top-grade Rathalos wing, removed in full. Such majesty befits the King of the Skies.

1279.name: Rathalos Mantle
1279.description: A legendary Rathalos scale. Those who craft it are said to rule the earth and seize the sky.

1280.name: A.Rathalos Shard
1280.description: An Azure Rathalos part made of several overlapping scales. It boasts beauty and strength.

1282.name: A.Rathalos Lash
1282.description: A top-grade Azure Rathalos tail. Strong ones like this are prized by all and sold at high prices.

1283.name: S.Rathalos Shard
1283.description: A Silver Rathalos part made of several overlapping scales. Makes for a nice silver accessory.

1284.name: S.Rath Cortex
1284.description: A heavy Silver Rathalos cortex. This legendary item shines like moonlight, even in darkness.

1472.name: Deviljho Shard
1472.description: A heavy, high-quality Deviljho scale. Rumored to bring bad luck, but actually an excellent material.

1475.name: Deviljho Ripper
1475.description: An incredibly sharp, rigid talon. Even experienced handlers can be injured if not careful.

1476.name: Deviljho Flail
1476.description: A large slab of a Deviljho's leech-like tail. Even so-called experts are shocked by it.

1477.name: Deviljho Crook
1477.description: An unsettling scale that became warped as it absorbed the malice of the Deviljho's various prey.

1479.name: Vile Fang
1479.description: A massive, overgrown fang that can chomp through anything. Filled with pure evil.

1480.name: Brach Cortex
1480.description: The thick cortex of a Brachydios. Its stoic beauty adds strength and dignity to equipment.

1483.name: Brach Pounder+
1483.description: The arm of an especially angry Brachydios. Strong and heavy, as if made of iron.

1485.name: Brach Pallium
1485.description: A legendary Brachydios shell. Those who craft it are said to rule the earth and seize the sky.

1486.name: Glowing Slime
1486.description: Highly explosive green slime found on a fierce Brachydios. Handle with extreme care.

1498.name: Lagombi Fur
1498.description: The very finest Lagombi fur, durable and yet surprisingly soft. A top-shelf item.

1499.name: Lagombi Auricle
1499.description: A superior Lagombi ear with astonishing hearing capabilities. An exceptional crafting material.

1501.name: Zinogre Cortex
1501.description: The teal cortex of a Zinogre. The monarch's armor crushes wills with its immense power.

1502.name: Zinogre Hardhorn
1502.description: A mighty Zinogre horn. None can sand before its sky-shattering, awe-inspiring power.

1505.name: Zinogre Lash
1505.description: A superior Zinogre tail that wields incomparable destructive power.

1512.name: S.Zinogre Lash
1512.description: A Stygian Zinogre's terrifyingly strong tail. Said to be able to slice through solid steel.

1536.name: Diablos Cortex
1536.description: The rigid cortex of a Diablos, both harder and sturdier than its carapace.

1537.name: Diablos Chine
1537.description: Tough Diablos backplate, strengthened by burning sands. An ideal material for armor.

1539.name: Diablos Hardhorn
1539.description: An especially elegant Diablos horn with almost perfect shape. An extremely rare material.

1542.name: B.Diablos Cortex
1542.description: A heavy Black Diablos cortex. Its weight reveals its overwhelming density and strength.

1543.name: B.Diablos Chine
1543.description: Finely honed Black Diablos backplate. Best described as black, hard, and heavy.

1557.name: Black Pearl
1557.description: The Hunting Fleet sometimes brings these back. The black glow fetches a high price.

1600.name: Conflagrant Sac
1600.description: A monster organ filled with a highly explosive powder. Extremely dangerous!

1601.name: Flood Sac
1601.description: A monster organ designed to hold and preserve tremendous amounts of water.

1602.name: Cryo Sac
1602.description: A monster organ that has fierce freezing properties. It can coat an area in ice in a flash.

1603.name: Lightning Sac
1603.description: A monster organ that can store electricity as strong as lightning. It rumbles like thunder.

1604.name: Omniplegia Sac
1604.description: A monster organ filled with potent neurotoxins. A single touch can cause paralysis.

1605.name: Coma Sac
1605.description: A monster organ that contains dangerous powder. One whiff can induce a coma.

1606.name: Fey Wyvern Gem
1606.description: An exceptionally pure gem taken from a bird wyvern. Its fragility makes it difficult to carve.

1611.name: Monster Slogbone
1611.description: An incredibly strong bone harvested from a fearsome wyvern. Its heft is impressive.

1613.name: Massive Bone
1613.description: An impossibly hard bone from a large beast. It exceeds all known standards for crafting material.

1614.name: Prized Pelt
1614.description: A pelt from a small animal. Used for many things, but mostly just regular clothes.

1615.name: Rhenoplos Bone
1615.description: As strong as it is heavy, this Rhenoplos bone is well-suited for use in crafting armor.

1616.name: Avian Stoutbone
1616.description: The robust bone of a bird wyvern. Durable and easy to craft with this.

1619.name: Crushing Fang
1619.description: The strongest fang of a fanged beast. It can pierce a monsters's shell as if it were paper.

1624.name: Monster Essence
1624.description: A broth made from only the thickest, choicest parts of a monster's juices. Gross?

1629.name: Emperor Hopper
1629.description: A grasshopper with an exceptionally strong shell. Prized as a crafting material.

1630.name: Flutterfly
1630.description: A butterfly with shimmering wings. So rarely seen in the wild, many believe it to be a myth.

1635.name: Eltalite Ore
1635.description: A promising new ore that produces higher quality metal than Carbalite Ore.

1636.name: Meldspar Ore
1636.description: An ore composed of a durable, flexible metal that works well as a combining agent.

1637.name: Allfire Stone
1637.description: An ore that blazes with an all-consuming flame. Requires considerable skill to mine.

1638.name: Purecrystal
1638.description: A crystal that's 100% pure. Hard enough to be used in workshop tools.

1654.name: Gloamgrass Bud
1654.description: A night-blooming flower from a special herb native to Moga. It may have healing properties.

1715.name: Dust of Life
1715.description: A medicine with strone curative properties. Studied in secret, it is said to restore youth.

1719.name: VE Cosmic Ticket
1719.description: A ticket awarded for hunting with friends. The Veggie Elder may offer an amazing trade...

1720.name: Conqueror's Seal
1720.description: Proof you have overcome countless trials, and a true badge of honor.

1750.name: Qurupeco Shard
1750.description: A strong scale concealed by vivid plumage, grown to full maturity over many years.

1751.name: Lustrous Feather
1751.description: A vivid feather with an elegant luster. Qurupeco with these only live in certain regions.

1753.name: Gobul Piel
1753.description: Thick skin from a Gobul. Too rubbery for eating, but perfect for crafting equipment.

1754.name: Gobul Surspike
1754.description: An unusual barb from a Gobul. Only the most formidable of the breed have such precious spikes.

1756.name: Arzuros Cortex
1756.description: A superior Arzuros cortext. This highly-developed shell is a huge thorn in all hunters' sides.

1758.name: Dazzling Fluid
1758.description: A sparkling fluid with impressive water-retention ability. Improves performance and style.

1762.name: Barroth Cortex
1762.description: A Barroth's cortex. Years worth of mud have hardened it beyond all measure.

1763.name: Barroth Crown
1763.description: The heavy scalp of a formidable Barroth. As hard to remove as it is durable.

1765.name: Volvidon Cortex
1765.description: A heavy Volvidon cortext. Difficult to forge with, but can produce genuinely powerful gear.

1766.name: Agnaktor Cortex
1766.description: The rigid cortex of an Agnaktor. Highly heat-resistant, it produces bright red items when forged.

1768.name: J.Barroth Cortex
1768.description: The solid, ice-covered cortex of a Jade Barroth. The frosty coating is surprisngly strong.

1771.name: Durambolite
1771.description: A legendary gem rarely produced inside a Duramboros's body. Elegant, though gloomy.

1772.name: Uragaan Cortex
1772.description: An especially hard Uragaan cortex. Crafting with it can be a trying task, to say the least.

1773.name: Uragaan Pallium
1773.description: A legendary Uragaan shell. Those who craft it are said to rule the earth and seize the sky.

1776.name: Nargacuga Mantle
1776.description: A legendary Nargacuga scale. Those who craft it are said to rule the earth and seize the sky.

1777.name: Lagiacrus Shard
1777.description: The ultimate specimen of Lagiacrus Scale. Special skills are required to craft with it.

1778.name: Deathly Shocker
1778.description: A thick shell found on a select few Lagiacrus. It releases huge bolts of electricity.

1779.name: Lagiacrus Mantle
1779.description: A valuable azure scale found on select Lagiacrus. Said to greatly boost equipment performance.

1780.name: I.Lagi D-Shocker
1780.description: A thick shell seen only rarely on Ivory Lagiacrus. It can produce a veritable rain of thunderbolts.

1781.name: I.Lagi Hardhorn
1781.description: A fine horn from an Ivory Lagiacrus. Beloved by the rich for its flawless elegance.

1784.name: S.Uragaan Scute+
1784.description: A highly heat-resistant Steel Uragaan scute. Its rigidity makes it hard to use in forging.

1785.name: Ceadeus Scale
1785.description: Almost too large to be called a scale. Not as hard as you might think.

1787.name: Deep Dragongem
1787.description: One of the hardest materials to reap from a Ceadeus. Its center is a bottomless void.

1791.name: Mohran Rockskin
1791.description: A heavy shell piece taken from a Jhen Mohran. It surpasses even steel in strength.

1792.name: Mohran Allbrace
1792.description: A thick, high quality brace from a Jhen Mohran. Easy craftable with the right amount of force.

1793.name: Deific Fang
1793.description: A beautiful fang with a divine aura. Its shape and color best other Jhen Mohran fangs.

1797.name: Miralis Scale
1797.description: A fiery black scale from a Dire Miralis. Also called the burning flower for its eerie beauty.

1798.name: Miralis Smelter
1798.description: A burning hot core from a Dire Miralis's hips. A magma-like substance swirls inside it.

1799.name: Dire Dragongem
1799.description: A legendary gem expelled from the body of a Dire Miralis. It formed from crystallized magma.

1800.name: A.Lagi D-Shocker
1800.description: A thick shell from an Abyssal Lagiacrus's back. Turns the sea itself into an electrified weapon.

1801.name: A.Lagi Dynamo
1801.description: An unknown Abyssal Lagiacrus organ. Rumored to be the source of the monster's electricity.

1803.name: Cloudy Moonshard
1803.description: The moon-like bladewing of a Lucent Nargacuga. He who crafts it controls the night.

1810.name: Alatreon Mantle
1810.description: The mantle of an Alatreon is the stuff of legend, containing traces of every element within.
